dians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As a result, the Canadian Olympic Committee instead said the team would be guided by assistant coach Andy Spence.\", \"from\": 543, \"to\": 656, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 560, \"end\": 586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Canadian Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 644, \"end\": 655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Spence\", \"score\": 0.9999899697693844, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andy Spence\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Spence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Spence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Priestman had already removed herself from the sidelines for the team's opening game against New Zealand, which Canada went on to win 2-1  Having denied any wrongdoing, she was expected to resume that role for the team's second group game before COC said new information had come to light.\", \"from\": 658, \"to\": 947, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 751, \"end\": 762, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9433744739828261, \"rank\": 0.05584798706923435, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 770, \"end\": 776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9988091506719461, \"rank\": 0.0010585629275670183, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/